{
  "texts": [
    "We assume that the irregular class Θ of V satisfies Assumption 4.1.",
    "If V has irregular class Θ and associated formal local system V 0 with graded pieces V 0 ⟨f ⟩ for the active circles ⟨f ⟩, then the V 0 ⟨f ⟩ can be viewed as local systems on the circles ⟨f ⟩.",
    "Therefore, they are determined by vector spaces K f I:= Γ(I, V 0 ⟨f ⟩) for any I ∈ A(f) and identifications κ I:",
    "J for any neighbouring sectors I, J ∈ A(f), where J follows I with respect to the given orientation.",
    "Note that K f I is naturally identified with (V 0 ⟨f ⟩) m I for the midpoint m I of I."
  ]
}